problemStatement:
You are given a function `readFileCallback` that uses a callback. Your task is to create a promisified version `readFilePromise` that returns a promise. Then use both to read a file and log its content.

```javascript
// Callback version (simulated)
function readFileCallback(path, cb) {
  // Simulate async file read
  setTimeout(() => {
    if (path === 'data.txt') {
      cb(null, 'file content');
    } else {
      cb('File not found');
    }
  }, 500);
}
```

Write `readFilePromise` that wraps this. Then call it with `'data.txt'` and handle the result with `.then` and `.catch`. Also try with a non-existent file to test error handling.

solutionCode:
function readFilePromise(path) {
  return new Promise((resolve, reject) => {
    readFileCallback(path, (err, data) => {
      if (err) reject(err);
      else resolve(data);
    });
  });
}

readFilePromise('data.txt')
  .then(data => console.log(data))
  .catch(err => console.error('Error:', err));

readFilePromise('missing.txt')
  .then(data => console.log(data))
  .catch(err => console.error('Error:', err));
